00:30:54.300 --> 00:30:55.506
I think they're shabby.

00:30:55.506 --> 00:30:57.140
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:57.640 --> 00:30:58.280
- OK.

00:30:58.280 --> 00:31:00.540
Onion-- I don't even
know what I got--

00:31:00.540 --> 00:31:02.880
cucumber, tomato,
Kalamata olives.

00:31:02.880 --> 00:31:06.380
We're basically making
a standard Greek salad.

00:31:06.380 --> 00:31:07.110
- All right.

00:31:07.110 --> 00:31:08.400
- We take some feta cheese.

00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:10.012
I love to buy the
block feta cheese.

00:31:10.012 --> 00:31:11.970
I can hear the crew back
there going, this guy,

00:31:11.970 --> 00:31:14.176
it's his last day for sure.

00:31:14.176 --> 00:31:15.550
- They've been
around a long time

00:31:15.550 --> 00:31:17.216
because they don't
talk to us like that.

00:31:17.216 --> 00:31:18.636
[END PLAYBACK]

00:31:18.636 --> 00:31:20.234
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:22.980
SAM ZIEN: So my
editor's with me there.

00:31:22.980 --> 00:31:24.360
We leave.

00:31:24.360 --> 00:31:27.390
We go for brunch or breakfast.

00:31:27.390 --> 00:31:29.940
And there's no talk about
that being problematic.

00:31:29.940 --> 00:31:31.350
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:32.680 --> 00:31:34.680
There's no talking about
that being problematic.

00:31:34.680 --> 00:31:37.710
He just goes, look, it's just
another good "Today Show"

00:31:37.710 --> 00:31:39.380
appearance.

00:31:39.380 --> 00:31:42.330
So the "Today Show,"
they send a car

00:31:42.330 --> 00:31:45.030
to take you back to the
airport and I'm in the car.

00:31:45.030 --> 00:31:48.330
And my wife, who's
now a few hours

00:31:48.330 --> 00:31:51.780
ahead of me or behind,
she's now watched it.

00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:53.520
And now people are texting her.

00:31:53.520 --> 00:31:55.680
And she's texting me, oh my god.

00:31:55.680 --> 00:31:56.510
I go, what?

00:31:56.510 --> 00:31:57.780
She goes, I can't believe
what they're saying.

00:31:57.780 --> 00:31:58.660
I go, what are they saying?

00:31:58.660 --> 00:32:00.284
She goes, they're
saying you're a hero.

00:32:00.284 --> 00:32:01.680
I go, a hero for what?

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:04.150
She goes, for telling Kathie
Lee Gifford to shut up.

00:32:04.150 --> 00:32:05.330
I go, I never said shut up.

00:32:05.330 --> 00:32:06.480
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:06.480 --> 00:32:09.786
I said, please, please
can I talk one minute?

00:32:09.786 --> 00:32:11.910
She goes, well, they think
you did something great.

00:32:11.910 --> 00:32:14.310
I go, this can't go well for me.

00:32:14.310 --> 00:32:16.410
So anyway, that was a Thursday.

00:32:16.410 --> 00:32:18.610
By Saturday, Sunday,
it had been online.

00:32:18.610 --> 00:32:20.520
It had been watched
like 50,000 times.

00:32:20.520 --> 00:32:24.150
Now, it's at 1.7 million
or something like that.

00:32:24.150 --> 00:32:25.930
I go to Seattle two
weeks after that.

00:32:25.930 --> 00:32:26.940
And I get off the
plane in Seattle

00:32:26.940 --> 00:32:28.648
and there's a text
from the "Today Show."

00:32:28.648 --> 00:32:30.070
Hey, we'd like you to come back.

00:32:30.070 --> 00:32:30.840
I go, great.

00:32:30.840 --> 00:32:31.470
Can you call?

00:32:31.470 --> 00:32:35.820
So I call and they go,
that segment was great

00:32:35.820 --> 00:32:37.590
and it generated a lot of buzz.

00:32:37.590 --> 00:32:39.600
We'd like you to come
in and address it

00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:47.506
with them and we'll have a
coach here to deal with--

00:32:47.506 --> 00:32:48.500
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:50.700
An etiquette coach.

00:32:50.700 --> 00:32:51.870
So they had a good coach.

00:32:51.870 --> 00:32:53.190
That was my third time.

00:32:53.190 --> 00:32:54.710
It's not been watched very much.

00:32:54.710 --> 00:32:56.910
It was awkward AF.

00:32:56.910 --> 00:32:58.980
I'm telling you,
Kathie Lee Gifford

00:32:58.980 --> 00:33:01.507
stood beside me and in
the middle of my talking--

00:33:01.507 --> 00:33:03.840
so there was this little
conversation with the etiquette

00:33:03.840 --> 00:33:06.540
coach and then goodbye,
and then I'm cooking.

00:33:06.540 --> 00:33:08.010
And she's standing beside me.

00:33:08.010 --> 00:33:09.300
She's rubbing my face.

00:33:09.300 --> 00:33:11.340
She goes, are we
making you nervous?

00:33:11.340 --> 00:33:13.347
She wasn't making me
nervous, it was just weird.

00:33:13.347 --> 00:33:15.180
And then she takes her
fingers and puts them

00:33:15.180 --> 00:33:18.034
underneath my armpit.

00:33:18.034 --> 00:33:19.450
And she goes, oh,
you're sweating.

00:33:19.450 --> 00:33:22.290
OK, A, I had like two
layers of clothing on.

00:33:22.290 --> 00:33:24.610
So no, that wouldn't
have been possible.

00:33:24.610 --> 00:33:26.940
B, I'm a Jewish male.

00:33:26.940 --> 00:33:28.031
We don't sweat.

00:33:28.031 --> 00:33:28.530
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:28.530 --> 00:33:31.000
So it was just creepy.

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:36.000
Anyway, I've been there 12
times in total, every other time

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:37.110
not with them.

00:33:37.110 --> 00:33:39.540
They've always put me
with somebody else.

00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:42.180
But one of the upshots of
this is I get a phone call

00:33:42.180 --> 00:33:45.300
from a producer at the Stern
show one day, who said, boy, we

00:33:45.300 --> 00:33:46.830
just found that clip.

00:33:46.830 --> 00:33:48.284
So here's just
the audio of that.

00:33:48.284 --> 00:33:49.575
HOWARD STERN: What's this clip?

00:33:49.575 --> 00:33:49.844
ROBIN QUIVERS: [INAUDIBLE]

00:33:49.844 --> 00:33:51.969
HOWARD STERN: A cook telling
Kathie Lee to be quiet

00:33:51.969 --> 00:33:52.727
today on--

00:33:52.727 --> 00:33:54.060
ROBIN QUIVERS: Let me hear that.

00:33:54.060 --> 00:33:56.180
HOWARD STERN: Whoever
this is, is a genius,

00:33:56.180 --> 00:33:57.060
if this is for real.

00:33:57.060 --> 00:33:57.770
Let me hear this.

00:34:03.480 --> 00:34:07.340
The cook's name is Sam
Zien, Z-I-E-N, Zien.

00:34:07.340 --> 00:34:09.800
And his website is
thecookingguy.com.

00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:11.219
And he is my hero.

00:34:11.219 --> 00:34:13.070
And I love this guy.

00:34:13.070 --> 00:34:15.326
And I think he's a real man.

00:34:15.326 --> 00:34:18.239
And too bad he had to do the mea
culpas back there afterwards.

00:34:18.239 --> 00:34:19.080
He shouldn't have.

00:34:19.080 --> 00:34:21.380
ROBIN QUIVERS: But he
still kept it light.

00:34:21.380 --> 00:34:22.354
He's an entertainer.

00:34:22.354 --> 00:34:24.270
HOWARD STERN: That is
the greatest single clip

00:34:24.270 --> 00:34:27.339
that should be played
every day on this show.

00:34:27.339 --> 00:34:28.860
[LAUGHTER]

00:34:29.339 --> 00:34:31.380
SAM ZIEN: All right, my
moment on the Stern show.

00:34:31.380 --> 00:34:33.270
And by the way, I'm a
huge Howard Stern fan.

00:34:33.270 --> 00:34:35.580
Anybody else?

00:34:35.580 --> 00:34:37.120
You got the new app?

00:34:37.120 --> 00:34:38.996
Video, it's got video.

00:34:38.996 --> 00:34:39.960
It's great.

00:34:39.960 --> 00:34:41.909
Anyway.

00:34:41.909 --> 00:34:45.480
So then the
publisher comes back.

00:34:45.480 --> 00:34:47.670
They want two more books.

00:34:47.670 --> 00:34:48.405
We do the books.

00:34:52.370 --> 00:34:56.530
Look, the point of the story
for me is really simple.

00:34:56.530 --> 00:34:58.750
I just wanted to be happy.

00:34:58.750 --> 00:35:01.320
I say to people, the
guy that you see on TV,

00:35:01.320 --> 00:35:04.230
and hopefully the guy you're
seeing now, is the same person.

00:35:04.230 --> 00:35:05.880
There's no fake.

00:35:05.880 --> 00:35:11.190
There's not one on-camera
persona and then another one.

00:35:11.190 --> 00:35:12.030
There's just me.

00:35:12.030 --> 00:35:13.750
If you like me,
great, watch the show.

00:35:13.750 --> 00:35:16.590
If you don't like me,
don't watch the show.

00:35:16.590 --> 00:35:19.050
And honestly, you don't need
to send me an email telling me

00:35:19.050 --> 00:35:20.100
why you don't like me.

00:35:20.100 --> 00:35:20.730
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:20.730 --> 00:35:23.560
I don't need that.

00:35:23.560 --> 00:35:26.910
I have a-- getting to be
a robust YouTube channel.

00:35:26.910 --> 00:35:30.930
And with that
comes the comments.

00:35:30.930 --> 00:35:31.979
You're this, you're that.

00:35:31.979 --> 00:35:33.520
You can't do this,
you can't do that.

00:35:33.520 --> 00:35:34.478
I watched that episode.

00:35:34.478 --> 00:35:35.010
It sucked.

00:35:35.010 --> 00:35:36.390
Then I watched that
one and it sucked.

00:35:36.390 --> 00:35:38.250
And then I watched
that one and it sucked.

00:35:38.250 --> 00:35:40.270
I mean, stop watching
me, for God's sakes.

00:35:40.270 --> 00:35:41.930
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:42.430 --> 00:35:43.905
But the concept of--

00:35:43.905 --> 00:35:45.960
look, in the beginning,
I cut myself a lot.

00:35:45.960 --> 00:35:50.250
I burned myself a lot because
I didn't know what I was doing.

00:35:50.250 --> 00:35:54.522
It's that 10,000 hours concept.

00:35:54.522 --> 00:35:56.480
You do something enough,
you get to do it well.

00:35:56.480 --> 00:35:59.970
My third cookbook, I wrote,
cooking is like riding a bike.

00:35:59.970 --> 00:36:02.080
The more you do it,
the better you get.

00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:04.780
The reality is, everything
is like riding a bike.

00:36:04.780 --> 00:36:08.440
The first time we all rode a
bike, the same thing happened.

00:36:08.440 --> 00:36:10.290
We fell off and
we hurt ourselves.

00:36:10.290 --> 00:36:13.200
And a day later or maybe that
afternoon, you finally get up

00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:14.640
and you can ride a bike.

00:36:14.640 --> 00:36:19.350
First time you make a
pineapple upside-down cake,

00:36:19.350 --> 00:36:20.580
maybe you burn it.

00:36:20.580 --> 00:36:22.800
Maybe you follow
the recipe to the T

00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:26.670
and 350 for 55
minutes in your oven

00:36:26.670 --> 00:36:29.760
is wrong because your
oven is not calibrated.

00:36:29.760 --> 00:36:32.209
It's really 385.

00:36:32.209 --> 00:36:33.750
Who knows what their
oven temperature

00:36:33.750 --> 00:36:36.880
is unless you have a little
thing that will calibrate?

00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:38.620
So what's the point?

00:36:38.620 --> 00:36:40.852
The point is, when
you do something,

00:36:40.852 --> 00:36:42.810
you should enjoy it
because you'll do it better

00:36:42.810 --> 00:36:43.660
than anybody else.

00:36:43.660 --> 00:36:44.160
That's true.

00:36:44.160 --> 00:36:46.701
There's that book, "Do What You
Love, The Money Will Follow."

00:36:46.701 --> 00:36:48.690
I say it should be
called "Do What You Love,

00:36:48.690 --> 00:36:50.065
You'll Be Really Damn Happy."

00:36:50.065 --> 00:36:51.440
And then maybe
the money follows.

00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:52.860
And if it does, it's a bonus.

00:36:52.860 --> 00:36:55.320
But literally on the
last day on this planet,

00:36:55.320 --> 00:36:57.030
nobody's going to
remember the money.

00:36:57.030 --> 00:36:59.250
You're going to remember
how you feel inside.

00:36:59.250 --> 00:37:01.180
And that's really
all that matters.

00:37:01.180 --> 00:37:05.070
The last thing I'll
show you is my now demo.

00:37:05.070 --> 00:37:07.740
I wish it didn't stutter,
but it's my demo from today.

00:37:07.740 --> 00:37:12.030
And now, after all these
years, I found out who I was.

00:37:12.030 --> 00:37:15.210
That first demo you saw, I had
all my food all chopped up,

00:37:15.210 --> 00:37:17.340
pre-prepped in little
bowls in front of me

00:37:17.340 --> 00:37:20.010
because that's what cooking
shows did in those days.

00:37:20.010 --> 00:37:21.540
You had all that stuff set.

00:37:21.540 --> 00:37:23.550
And I didn't know to be myself.

00:37:23.550 --> 00:37:26.500
I just knew to try and
be like everybody else.

00:37:26.500 --> 00:37:27.430
It took me awhile.

00:37:27.430 --> 00:37:29.160
I finally got it figured out.

00:37:29.160 --> 00:37:30.060
And now, I'm happy.

00:37:30.060 --> 00:37:31.140
It's me.

00:37:31.140 --> 00:37:31.980
It works.

00:37:31.980 --> 00:37:33.030
You like me, great.

00:37:33.030 --> 00:37:35.730
If you don't like me,
please don't watch.

00:37:35.730 --> 00:37:37.350
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:37.350 --> 00:37:39.030
Unless you have
one of those boxes

00:37:39.030 --> 00:37:43.800
that measures audience watching,
and then watch me and then

00:37:43.800 --> 00:37:44.520
turn it off.

00:37:44.520 --> 00:37:46.442
But don't email me.

00:37:46.442 --> 00:37:47.930
Here we go.

00:37:47.930 --> 00:37:48.979
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:37:48.979 --> 00:37:50.270
- Hey, I'm Sam the cooking guy.

00:37:50.270 --> 00:37:51.728
And this is about
me showing people

00:37:51.728 --> 00:37:54.800
how to make regular, everyday,
but really good food.

00:37:54.800 --> 00:37:58.150
[CHUCKLES] Look at
them going already.

00:37:58.150 --> 00:38:00.117
Little bit more
pepper for color.

00:38:00.117 --> 00:38:00.700
And that's it.

00:38:00.700 --> 00:38:02.200
Wow.

00:38:02.200 --> 00:38:03.460
Man, is that good.

00:38:03.460 --> 00:38:05.710
Tell me that doesn't look
beautiful and pretty and

00:38:05.710 --> 00:38:06.520
amazing.

00:38:06.520 --> 00:38:08.680
Look at the colors
in this scene.

00:38:08.680 --> 00:38:10.210
That, you just put that out.

00:38:10.210 --> 00:38:13.110
And I mean food that
anyone can make, anyone.

00:38:13.110 --> 00:38:13.840
That's a burger.

00:38:13.840 --> 00:38:14.950
Look at that.

00:38:14.950 --> 00:38:17.110
This is a very pretty pizza.

00:38:17.110 --> 00:38:19.780
Why do I now have to start
mixing my own dressing?

00:38:19.780 --> 00:38:21.280
You can if you want to.

00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:23.890
I'm here to teach you things
that you can do quickly

00:38:23.890 --> 00:38:24.430
and simply.

